HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 388
BY REPRESENTATIVE MCFARLAND
A RESOLUTION
To commend Wade Dubea on the occasion of his retirement from state service.
WHEREAS, Wade Dubea is a resident of New Roads and is married to Marjorie
Dubea, with whom he has two daughters and two granddaughters; he and his wife are
passionate about learning and teaching about the environment and nature, and he has been
able to share this love through his storied career in forestry; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Dubea graduated with a bachelor of science degree in forestry from
Louisiana State University; he returned to LSU to enter the College of Education's
Alternative Certification program, where he earned a Louisiana Teacher Certification in
secondary science; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Dubea's career included work as a high school teacher and
professional forester for private timber companies; after graduating from LSU, he worked
as a forester in Texas and Louisiana, and his responsibilities included timber production,
assessment, and mapping; as an educator, he taught biology and environmental science at
a Baton Rouge high school; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Dubea joined the staff of the Louisiana Department of Agriculture
and Forestry in 2001; he began as a forester in the Louisiana Forest Inventory Analysis
Program and was promoted to the role of director of the Education Program; as director, he
